From Wednesday 8 May to Monday 13 May, a 477-tonne oversized and overmass (OSOM) load carrying a large power transformer will be moving between Albury and Colongra on the Central Coast. Motorists are being advised of changed traffic conditions as the oversized vehicle travels along the Hume Hwy at a reduced speed. 

  • Wednesday 8 May – From Albury to Coolac, along the Hume Highway, between 10pm and 5:30am (Thursday).
  • Thursday 9 May – From Coolac to Goulburn, along the Hume Highway, between 10pm and 4:30am (Friday).
  • Friday 10 May – From Goulburn to Campbelltown along the Hume Highway between 10pm and 5am (Saturday).
  • Saturday 11 May – From Campbelltown to Mooney Mooney along the Hume Motorway/M7/M2/M1 between 11pm and 4:30am (Sunday). 
  • Monday 13 May – From Mooney Mooney to Colongra along the M1 Pacific Motorway between 12am and 4:30am. 

Motorists are urged to slow down and to exercise caution when attempting to pass the oversized vehicle. Traffic controllers escorting the vehicle will direct motorists.
